WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en-GB

1
00:00:00.433 --> 00:00:04.333
How to switch to a domain (for existing Knox Guard customers)

2
00:00:04.933 --> 00:00:07.016
As an existing Knox Guard customer,

3
00:00:07.016 --> 00:00:09.341
you'll be prompted to select a domain tenant 

4
00:00:09.341 --> 00:00:12.332
when you sign into the console as a super admin.

5
00:00:12.333 --> 00:00:15.078
The domain selection screen appears immediately 

6
00:00:15.078 --> 00:00:17.099
after launching the Knox Guard console. 

7
00:00:17.400 --> 00:00:18.833
If you select "Finish later",

8
00:00:19.100 --> 00:00:22.785
then you'll see a persistent notification at the top of your Knox Guard console 

9
00:00:22.785 --> 00:00:24.432
until you make the switch.

10
00:00:24.800 --> 00:00:28.666
Once you initiate the switch, you'll be taken to the "Domain selection" page.

11
00:00:29.233 --> 00:00:32.129
To learn about the characteristics of each domain type,

12
00:00:32.129 --> 00:00:34.965
see the "Intro to domains" video in this series.

13
00:00:35.166 --> 00:00:37.360
Review the available domain options and

14
00:00:37.360 --> 00:00:39.869
select the one that best suits your business needs.

15
00:00:39.870 --> 00:00:43.299
Note that once you select a domain type, it is irreversible. 

16
00:00:44.033 --> 00:00:46.266
If you select the "Device Financing" domain,

17
00:00:46.466 --> 00:00:48.815
additional setup steps will be required.

18
00:00:48.815 --> 00:00:50.608
You can learn more about these additional steps

19
00:00:50.609 --> 00:00:53.799
in the "How to select the Device Financing domain" video.

20
00:00:54.200 --> 00:00:56.618
When switching to a Device Financing domain, 

21
00:00:56.618 --> 00:00:59.426
you can choose to either apply Hardened Security mode

22
00:00:59.427 --> 00:01:01.535
to your current devices immediately,

23
00:01:01.536 --> 00:01:03.032
or apply it at a later time 

24
00:01:03.033 --> 00:01:04.799
by going to the "Policies" page,

25
00:01:04.966 --> 00:01:06.899
then selecting "Hardened Security mode". 

26
00:01:07.833 --> 00:01:10.099
Note that once Hardened Security mode is applied,

27
00:01:10.366 --> 00:01:13.032
this option will disappear from the "Policies" page.

28
00:01:13.633 --> 00:01:16.712
After making your domain selection, click OK.

29
00:01:16.713 --> 00:01:20.268
Your Knox Guard tenant will be assigned to your selected domain,

30
00:01:20.268 --> 00:01:22.799
and you can continue to use the service as usual.

31
00:01:23.433 --> 00:01:26.499
A few key things to note about switching to a Knox Guard domain:

32
00:01:26.866 --> 00:01:29.733
Domain selection is only available to Knox Guard accounts

33
00:01:29.734 --> 00:01:31.456
configured as "Normal" tenants. 

34
00:01:31.456 --> 00:01:35.265
If your existing Knox Guard account was configured as a "Pay-as-you-go" tenant, 

35
00:01:35.633 --> 00:01:40.133
then you'll automatically be transitioned to the "Device Financing" domain after signing in.

36
00:01:41.300 --> 00:01:45.599
To learn more about Knox Guard domains, check out the other videos in this series, 

37
00:01:45.599 --> 00:01:49.644
or review our documentation at docs.samsungknox.com. 

38
00:01:49.645 --> 00:01:50.932
Thanks for watching!

